      • replaceNull

        protected String replaceNull(String val)
        Method that replaces common, literal NULL values with real nulls. For example you often find "null", "NULL" or "\N" as values in text files. This method is not used by the value() methods under the hood to allow access to raw data in case NULL makes sense.
        Returns:
        the input string or null in case its a literal form of NULL
